<h1>iOS or Android?</h1>
<p>"What's best" always depends on what you want to do. This is my impression of which of iOS and Android is better in different circumstances:</p>

<table>
<tr><td>Lowest cost</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>Any specific single feature (best camera, dual-sim, FM radio, etc.)</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>Best build quality</td><td>iOS</td></tr>
<tr><td>Easy to modify</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>Secure from other people modifying it without you knowing</td><td>iOS</td></tr>
<tr><td>Smart Watch</td><td>iOS</td></tr>
<tr><td>Smart Watch if you don't like the Apple Watch</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>Virtual Reality</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>Voice control interface</td><td>Android</td></tr>
<tr><td>MacOS integration</td><td>iOS</td></tr>
<tr><td>Meaningful choice of web browsers</td><td>Android</td></tr>
</table>

